column4:
two pillars;
two pieces for the top of each pillar, with the shape of big bowls;
rows of chains on the tops of the pillars

Solomon's workers also made all these things for God's temple:
the gold altar;
the tables which had the special bread on them

the gold images of flowers;
the lamps;
the small tools that held things for the altar

the small tools of pure gold that they used for the lamps;
the bowls for water;
the dishes for ashes;
the baskets that carried hot coals;
the gold pieces that held the doors of the Most Holy Place;
the gold pieces that held the doors of the temple's big hall.

Philistine soldiers had also attacked towns in the low hills in the west of Judah and in the Negev in the south. They took these towns for themselves and they lived in them:
Beth-Shemesh, Aijalon, Gederoth;
Soco, Timnah and Gimzo with the villages around them.
